@startuml
title Episode Analysis & Chat Pipeline

|Analysis|
start
:User clicks "Analyze Episode";

:Download MP3 from RSS feed URL
-> audio/{episode_id}.mp3;

:Transcribe with <b>OpenAI Whisper</b>
-> full transcript text;

:Split transcript into sentences
using <b>NLTK</b> sent_tokenize;

:Compute sentence embeddings,
group into <b>topic segments</b> via
sliding-window cosine similarity;

fork
  :Summarize each segment
  -> topic title and full topic summary;
fork again
  :Summarize full transcript
  -> full episode summary;
end fork

:Pre-compute <b>chat embeddings</b>:
chunk transcript and calculate embeddings for each chunk;

:Store in DB:
- episodes: transcript, summary,
  audio file path, duration, <b>chunks (JSON)</b>,
  <b>chunk_embeddings (binary)</b>
- episode_segments: per-segment
  topic + summary + transcript;

stop

|Chat|
start
:User asks a question;

:Load <b>pre-computed</b> chunks +
embeddings from DB;

:Calculate embedding for the <b>question</b>;

:Rank chunks by cosine similarity,
pick <b>top 3</b>;

:Prompt <b>LLM model</b>:
"Answer based ONLY on this context:
{top 3 chunks}";

:Return answer, persist both
messages to episode_chat;

stop

@enduml
